<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
Mexico (Chiapas, Colima, Guerrero, Morelos), Belize, Panama, Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3731.1.1" author="Segura, MO" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 57" refId="B88" refString="Segura, MO, dos Passos, MIS, Fonseca-Gessner, AA, Froehlich, CG, 2013. Elmidae Curtis, 1830 (Coleoptera, Polyphaga, Byrrhoidea) of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa 3731 (1): 1 - 57, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3731.1.1" title="Elmidae Curtis, 1830 (Coleoptera, Polyphaga, Byrrhoidea) of the Neotropical region." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3731.1.1" volume="3731" year="2013">Segura et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" author="Jaech, MA" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" refId="B49" refString="Jaech, MA, Kodada, J, Brojer, M, Shepard, W, Ciampor, JrF, 2016. Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol.14. Brill, Leiden, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" title="Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 14." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). A previous altitudinal record of 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. bufo" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" rank="species" species="bufo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="301">X. bufo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is from 1,219 m (
<bibRefCitation author="Hinton, HE" journalOrPublisher="Novitates Zoologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="217 - 396" publicationUrl="http://biostor.org/reference/85607" refId="B42" refString="Hinton, HE, 1940b. A monographic revision of the Mexican water beetles of the Family Elmidae. Novitates Zoologicae 42 (2): 217 - 396, http://biostor.org/reference/85607" title="A monographic revision of the Mexican water beetles of the Family Elmidae." url="http://biostor.org/reference/85607" volume="42" year="1940 b">Hinton 1940b</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, the species was found at all sampling levels (670-1,776 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Collected on substrates of gravel, macrophytes, and leaf packs, throughout the sampling months (February 2018 through February 2019, dry and rainy season).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
